<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOME-SALES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VALLEY HOME SALES SLUMP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREGORY J. WILCOX 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Sales of single-family homes plunged 19.5 &UR;  &LR; percent
in the San Fernando Valley during July as an unseasonable cold
front buffeted the market, a trade group said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The sales slowdown, the biggest annual percentage drop since a
20.1 &UR;  &LR; percent decline in December 1995, reflects rising prices and
