   Rising prices have been pushing buyers, especially first-timers,
into the condominium market.
</P>
<P>
   During July, Realtors sold 396 condominiums, an increase of 35,
or 9.7 percent, from the year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
   The median price of $138,000 was a gain of 8.7 percent over the
past 12 months, the highest for a July since 1992.
</P>
<P>
   Even though the all-important single-family sector slumped last
month, agents remain upbeat.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a strong market with no signs of fundamental weakness
on the horizon. Indeed, this may represent the kind of activity
we'll see for several years to come -- very busy with just enough
restraint on resale prices to prevent them from rising into the
stratosphere,'' noted association President R.E. ``Mitch'' Davis.
