<HEADLINE>
BEAUTY BUZZ: DIFFERENT STROKES  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by clients of ``HIGH STYLE AND MORE.''
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, see end of text. 
 &HT;    
 By THE EDITORS OF W MAGAZINE 
 (Three color slides are available.) 
 From W magazine 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
 &HT;    
 VIDEO DIARY  
 &HT;    The house of Givenchy has gone futuristic with Oblique, a trio
of quirky fragrances encased in a remote control-shape package.
 &HT;    Rewind is a floral with notes of honey; Play is reminiscent of
soft drinks; and Fast Forward is spiked with melon peel and Chinese
pepper. Available at Sephora and Carson Pirie Scott.
 &HT;    
 YOURS TRULY  
 &HT;    Calvin Klein is at it again with Truth, a fragrance collection
meant to evoke the warmth of skin. Novelties include a special
bedtime scent and single-note oils that allow you to create your
own version of Truth.
 &HT;    
 DUE DATES  
 &HT;    If celebrity makeup artist Jeni Lee has her way, milk and
medicine won't be the only items that bear expiration dates.
Cosmetics, she insists, also spoil over time, so her namesake
makeup collection is date-stamped, urging that eye shadow be tossed
after a year and mascara after just six months. Available at Henri
Bendel.
 &HT;    
 c.2000 Fairchild Publications 
