<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ADVISORY-NEWHOUSE </SLUG>
  
 (ATTENTION EDITORS: This advisory describes the top offerings from
Newhouse News Service for Tuesday, AUGUST 8. For information about
purchasing articles as a ``separate-buy,'' contact Debra Weydert of
the New York Times Syndicate at 1-732-390-4480; fax, 732-390-4697;
e-mail: weyded(at)nytimes.com.)
<TEXT>
<P>
   CURATORS-POLS _ The 2000 presidential election is months off,
but room is already being made for its place in history. Long after
President Bush or President Gore leaves the White House, something
of this summer's conventions and our times will survive in the
Smithsonian museum's political collection -- already sizeable at
90,000 objects, some of them older than the presidency itself.
Photos. About 1,400
</P>
