<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington _ On Monday, USA TODAY headlined: Bush
over Gore by 17 points. On Tuesday, USA TODAY reported: Bush's lead
has almost disappeared. The sudden shift between Monday's weekend
poll and Tuesday's quickie reaction to Gore's selection of Sen.
Joseph Lieberman is likely to be repeated over and over during the
coming campaign. This is going to be a tight, closely-matched race
and the only poll that matters is on election day. By MARIANNE
MEANS.
</P>
