<P>
   OLY-SWIMSUITS (Indianapolis) _ When the Olympic trials begin
here on Wednesday, American swimmers will make as much news for
what they are wearing as for what records they set in preparation
for the 2000 Summer Games next month in Sydney, Australia. A
bodysuit that fits athletes from neck to toe and comes with sleeves
has revolutionized the sport, reducing drag through the water. At
least 10 world records have been set worldwide this year in the new
swim suits. Speedo's versioon is called the Fastskin suit, which
contains tiny, v-shaped ridges that allow water to pass over the
swimmer more efficiently. The super-stretch fabric also compresses
a swimmer's muscles, therefore reducing the buildup of lactic acid
that causes fatigue. Swimmers also say the suit lifts them higher
in the water and makes it easier to stroke. By Jere Longman.
</P>
