SAN FRANCISCO _  PALETTE  _ Chef George Morrone's tricolor
meditation on tomato soup at San Francisco's Fifth Floor restaurant
is just one of the more refined examples of the Technicolor
revolution in today's kitchens. With local markets overflowing with
white zucchini, striped beets, golden peppers and purple potatoes,
Bay Area cooking has never been more colorful. 
With recipes 
 By Janet Fletcher  
