SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; WALK-OAK &LR;  _ In 1969 when Philip Chu arrived in
Oakland's Chinatown fresh from Burma, the tiny immigrant district
wasn't much more than a handful of stores and restaurants. Now, the
district snakes out well past its core, filled with all sorts of
Asian and Filipino foods. Chu, now a highly regarded chef in
Oakland, uncovers its treasures on a walking tour. &QL;
