<P>
   WINE-COLUMN _ One wine importer who has carved a name for
himself above the others is Kermit Lynch, a wine fanatic who spends
half the year in France and half in Berkeley, Calif., where he runs
a retail shop. The rest of the time Lynch is tending to his import
business, focusing on French wines of character and breeding, many
from relatively obscure regions of France, and virtually all
distinctive and delicious. (Fisher, Dayton Daily News). 14. MOVED.
