</P>
<P>
   BBN-CHIPPER _ Chipper Jones is on the verge of signing a 6-year,
$90 million deal, putting him on par with the highest paid players
in baseball and the deal will be announced on Friday when the
Braves return home. Trying to confirm. (Rogers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HOTDOGS _ Marlins closer Antonio Alfonseca launched into his
usual post-save routine. He screamed, pounded his chest and pointed
toward the heavens. Then he glared into the Braves' dugout. The
problem with the whole episode, which took place July25 in Atlanta,
was that Alfonseca didn't register a save. Instead he struck out
Steve Sisco, a .111 hitter, in the eighth inning with the Marlins
losing 6-4. (Andrews, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   TRIBUTE PAGE
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FLAMETHROWERS 0809 _ Speed thrills. Always has. The hard
throwers always have awed baseball. The bringers of the heat. The
fastball pitchers. They are an integral part of the game's romance
and mystique. From old-timers such as Walter Johnson and ``Bullet''
Bob Feller to the speed demons of today _ Billy Koch, Randy Johnson
and Pedro Martinez _ velocity has been an important facet of the
sport. (Wilkinson, Atlanta journal-Constitution) Art includes a
colorful photo illustration and six photos of famous fastball
throwers of yesteryear and today.
</P>
