<P>
   PHONES _ ATLANTA _Local telephone service, the rather boring
plain jane element in communications compared to go-go cell phones
and red-hot long distance services, has suddenly become a new
battleground. Many players are emerging to take on BellSouth, none
more eager than the cable giant,
</P>
<P>
   MediaOne, backed by its tentative parent, AT&AMP;T. Yes, AT&AMP;T, old
Ma Bell who used to be everybody's phone company. The move by the
cable company into phones, oddly enough, is being helped along by
BellSouth, mostly in obedience to federal legislation. (Kanell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
