<P>
   &UR; EDITORS: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service is planning full coverage _
text, graphics and photos _ of the Democratic National Convention
in Los Angeles from Aug. 14 to Aug. 17.
</P>
<P>
   A biographical series on Vice President Al Gore, written by
Melinda Henneberger, has been filed during the last two months, and
the stories are available for retransmission. The slugs are:
GORE-BIO, GORE-BIO-COLLEGE and GORE-MILITARY; abridged versions and
photos are also available. For repeats, call 212-556-1927.
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times editors plan several pages of stories for
each day of the convention. The News Service will list these
stories on a daily convention budget (BC-DEM-BUDGET-NYT), which
will include all Times stories and will also spotlight stories from
Times partner and regional newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   --Early coverage will include a poll/profile of the convention
delegates by Adam Nagourney, comparing them to the general public
and to the GOP delegates, and a look at the Democratic platform.
</P>
<P>
   --Daily stories are scheduled to include: a convention ledeall
by Richard L. Berke (DEM-RDP-NYT), an analysis by R.W. Apple Jr.
(DEM-ASSESS-NYT), a convention diary column by Matthew Purdy and
Alex Kuczynski (DEM-DAIRY-NYT), a television critic's notebook by
Caryn James (DEM-TV-NOTEBOOK-NYT), the view from TV and the Web by
Rick Lyman (DEM-POLITICAL-SURFING-NYT), how successfully the
message is communicated by Peter Marks (DEM-MESSAGE-NYT), stories
on Hillary Clinton by Adam Nagourney, profiles of the speakers and
editorial columns from Times writers on political developments and
issues.
</P>
<P>
   --Plans for other stories include scene, color and insight
pieces on health care, taxes and the economy by New York Times
political writers Robin Toner, Todd S. Purdum, James Sterngold,
Adam Clymer and Kevin Sack, among others.
</P>
<P>
   --For Wednesday: a profile and assessment of Sen. Joseph
Lieberman's acceptance speech.
</P>
<P>
   --For Thursday: a Man in the News profile of Vice President Al
Gore by Melinda Henneberger and Frank Bruni.
</P>
<P>
   --For Friday: a deconstruction of Gore's acceptance speech.
</P>
<P>
   All convention stories will be filed in the ``p'' category and
will carry a convention designation in the slug; e.g.,
BC-DEM-GORE-NYT. All stories are for use by New York Times News
Service clients. Look for updated and more detailed advisories
closer to the opening of the convention.
</P>
