<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Woman hurt at Home Depot gets $1.24 million
 &HT;    By Patti Bond
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A Colorado jury has awarded $1.24 million to a woman who was
injured in 1997 when a metal rack hit her head at a Home Depot
store in Louisville, Colo.
</P>
<P>
   Marlo Rice, 32, of Golden, Colo., suffered permanent head
injuries when a rack of bedding plants fell on her in Home Depot's
garden department.
</P>
<P>
   Home Depot said a gust of wind knocked the rack on top of Rice.
Rice claimed the rack was unstable because several steel-framed
tables were leaning against it. The company declined comment
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta-based retailer also recently agreed to pay $500,000
to a New Jersey couple whose 3-year-old son was injured in a 1997
store accident. The boy was hit on the head when several boxes of
vinyl siding fell on him at a store in Mount Laurel, N.J.
</P>
