<P>
   FIREFIGHTER-WORKPLACE (Undated) _ Few people embody America's
ideals like its 1.1 million volunteer firefighters. Gritty,
charitable, self-reliant, they answer millions of calls for help
each year. And each year, thousands get hurt. It is then that many
discover that their generosity is not necessarily matched by the
society they serve. Disabled volunteer firefighters generally get
workers' compensation, but the benefits vary widely. Some states
match what career firefighters receive. Some pay less. Some pay
nothing. By Mary Williams Walsh.
</P>
