<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, AUGUST 9 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-LIEBERMAN-PROFILE-NYT (moved Monday, August 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, August 7
about Senator Joseph I. Lieberman misspelled his middle name and
the surname of his first wife. His middle name is Isadore, not
Isador. His wife was Elizabeth Haas, not Hass.
</P>
<P>
   BC-YUGOSLAVIA-KARADZIC-NYT (moved Sunday, August 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, August 6
about the former leader of the Bosnian Serbs, Radovan Karadzic, who
is a fugitive from arrest for war crimes, misidentified the
organization that controls the peacekeeping force that is seeking
him in Bosnia. It is NATO, not the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEXICO-CARDINAL-MURDER-NYT (moved Thursday, July 27)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, July 27
about a two-year review of the slaying of a Mexican cardinal in
1993 referred incorrectly to the conclusions of two bishops who
took part in the investigation. Unlike some Roman Catholic leaders,
the two bishops shared the view of prosecutors that the killing of
the cardinal, Juan Jesus Posadas Ocampo, occurred when drug
traffickers mistook him for a rival, and was not intentional.
</P>
<P>
   BC-COMPUTER-BRIEFS-NYT (moved Sunday, July 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 23
about an announcement by the technology entrepreneur James H. Clark
that he had bought a million shares of Microsoft stock referred
imprecisely to a comment made about him later, at the same industry
conference, by the venture capitalist John Doerr. Doerr's speech
described two categories of Silicon Valley entrepreneurs _
missionaries and mercenaries. It was in response to a question from
the moderator that Doerr said Clark would probably consider himself
a mercenary; Doerr did not characterize Clark that way unprompted.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-EYE-SURGERY-NYT (moved Monday, July 31)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, July 31
about laser eye surgery misstated the title of an optometrist who
often handles the patient care before and after Lasik surgery. He
is Dr. Arkady Selenow, not Mr.
</P>
</TEXT>
